Below I‚Äôll outline what I see as the pros/cons and useful strategies for each role.

I wrote this post though because when I talk to people about their careers I‚Äôm surprised at how often they focus on only
one of these paths without taking the time to consider other options. Often when they get advice, people tell them to
follow the path that they followed (as a YC partner and former founder, I‚Äôm very guilty of this).

I don‚Äôt attach value judgements to these three paths. In my ten years in The Bay Area I‚Äôve seen friends lead successful
