## **6.** **Applying to YC**

YC funds two batches of startups per year. One in the winter and one in the summer. While we take applications all year
long, we have an early and a regular submission deadline for specific batches.

Once you‚Äôre ready to work on your startup full time, you can [apply for the next
batch](https://www.ycombinator.com/apply/) of Y Combinator.

**Why Y Combinator?**

![](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/wWPuoajaLnN9VAnP1OAJOhx4-OmmHMG1_Jh-1P00KeIQXkbHXWn97HFAe-k_XMSoc1gg-EKO21VY4x6yXY0UG2mK9a0oZUyxpB_Fz9sPxUhQyfLTVjkcRzKclRBi1Jxg3Qa3y4vS)

**Lifetime Support**

The Y Combinator program doesn't end on demo day. We continue to assist founders from idea through IPO and beyond. YC
starts with teaching founders the basics of [starting a company](https://www.startupschool.org/), [finding
customers](https://www.ycombinator.com/companies/), [raising angel investments](https://demoday.ycombinator.com/), and
[hiring their first employees](https://www.workatastartup.com/). Then we help founders secure[ Series A and B
funding](https://blog.ycombinator.com/introducing-yc-series-a-batches/) [scale their
companies](https://blog.ycombinator.com/growth-stage-program/), and hire an executive team. Once a YC company has scaled
to a certain level, we may [invest in later stage rounds](https://www.ycombinator.com/continuity/).

**Community**

![](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/RUmwtzAKzrhKKUmImfd-ljRsqwgJ3-QLm6UbiJZXQLMIdpJVQjlBw__6ufzo0Xf6qaVgFhyZRFNFZRtuLpR7EaR0jTeNhEak5S3ukGD9rnYLpuZxRjs3b2qK35Aa5diHvXSyDspP)

Y Combinator boasts the strongest and deepest founder community in the world. For the 6,000+ YC alumni, there‚Äôs always
someone to help guide them through every stage of their business; and with over 3,000 companies funded, founders have a
built-in cohort of customers ready to try their products and services.

**Well Known Resources**

Being part of Y Combinator will give your company numerous advantages in a highly competitive market. YC companies tend
to raise more money from better investors and achieve higher valuations. Our applications are open to anyone ‚Äî you don‚Äôt
need to be well connected in the tech or investment world to be accepted. Our team dispenses meaningful advice on
everything from growth strategies to overcoming technical hurdles to communicating with press and media.

**Secret Resources**

![](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/XM8kIlBfwRtOEyURCxSWz9zOKo8yP4-l9Gp4UzYZRGTKstyT2CqDFL6OhymedHUQmx6RgG4EVjlg5RYvps7dqzPNljZA5tQs2MOffPNiHmsEOwyOgopfw_iE3GZs5N1d_I8KqfNw)

Some of the lesser known advantages to being part of Y Combinator are access to the massive, vibrant YC alumni network,
the YC-only hiring platform, [Work at a Startup](http://workatastartup.com/), plus better deals and more customers.

**What is a day in the life of a founder in the batch?**

Every day will have its own unique chaos. In general, expect to be writing code, talking to users, solving problems, and
participating in weekly batch events, group activities, and office hours.

**What does YC look for in companies and founders?**

There‚Äôs no magic template for creating founders or companies. We do, however, often find these qualities in the most
successful ones.

**Technical Ability**

We like to see teams that have the ability to build, usually that means having a technical founder.

**A Drive to Build**

We do fund ideas. About 60 percent of the companies we fund don‚Äôt have a launched product, but we like founders who have
an inclination for action and are making fast progress on what they‚Äôre working on.

**Persistence and Resilience**

A number of companies apply to YC multiple times before being accepted. These days, about 50 percent of the companies we
fund have applied more than once. If a founder applies a second time, it‚Äôs important they show they‚Äôve made progress on
their company. This signals a founder is serious about building a startup.

**What stage and sector does YC invest in?**

We have companies in each batch that don‚Äôt have a fully formed idea and companies that have millions of dollars in
revenue.

We invest in companies from a broad range of industries ranging from consumer apps to biotech to SAAS. See the whole
range of companies and industries [here](https://www.ycombinator.com/companies).

**What are the requirements to apply to YC?**

Y Combinator is open to everyone and [the application is free](https://www.ycombinator.com/apply/).

**Are there different requirements for international founders?**

There are no different requirements for international founders. For the Summer 2021 batch, about half of the companies
were internationally based.

**Do I need a business plan?**

You do not need a business plan to apply to YC. Our application process usually helps founders understand more about why
and what they are trying to build.

*Tip:* Be concise and explain your idea simply.

## **7.** **Alternatives to Starting a Startup**

If you‚Äôve decided that being a startup founder isn‚Äôt right for you, there are still many other avenues open in the tech
industry. Here‚Äôs a few resources that can help.

